The girl used the target as a target to raise funds for her sister: "It's okay to think of a flesh wound"-Xinhua
A girl in Wulin Square, Hangzhou, stood in front of a large wooden board with the words “Human target, ten yuan per arrow” written on the board.
Yesterday morning, a photo of “Hangzhou girl willing to be a ‘target'to raise money for her sister” maxed out the circle of friends.
The photo shows a girl in Wulin Square, Hangzhou, standing in front of a large wooden board slightly taller than a human. The words “Human target, ten yuan per arrow” are written on the wooden board, indicating that passers-by can use bows and arrows to shoot after paying.
This behavior caused a heated discussion among netizens.
Last night, the head of publicity of the Xiacheng Branch of the Hangzhou Municipal Public Security Bureau confirmed to a reporter from the Beijing News that the police confirmed that the girl had made such an extreme move after raising money for her sister, but this behavior was not worthy of promotion. After being warned, the girl had left the local police station yesterday.
Girls' street "archery target" fundraising was warned
In the picture posted on the Internet, a long-haired girl is standing in front of a large wooden board in the shape of ”a“. The words ”Human target, ten yuan per arrow" are written in black ink on the wooden board. Her bank account number and WeChat and Alipay accounts are written on another wooden board in front of her.
The picture caused controversy after it went online.
Some netizens believed that this move was a “beggar's begging behavior”, and many netizens expressed sympathy for it.
“We discovered the situation when we patrolled to the side of the square around 10 o'clock in the morning on the 23rd. There were already a lot of onlookers at that time.  ”
The police at the Tianshui police station near the incident site said in an interview with local media that there were two girls who set up the stall, both of whom were about 20 years old and dressed up as young and beautiful.
Among them, the girl who was the “human target” kept crying, begging passers-by to play this game; the other girl yelled for help on the side, saying that her friend's sister had leukemia and was in urgent need of surgery. Please help.
“We contacted the local police in Guizhou and learned that the girl was raising money for her sister's leukemia treatment.  ”
Last night, the head of publicity of the Xiacheng Branch of the Hangzhou Municipal Public Security Bureau told a reporter from the Beijing News that the girl's name was Ji Jiali and she was raising funds for her sister Ji Jiayan.
However, since the treatment still costs more than 300,000 yuan, I couldn't think of a good way to raise funds for a while, so I made this behavior.
He said that during the whole process, one of the two girls was the target and the other was responsible for shooting, but they did not participate in it. No one was found to shoot arrows during the whole process, but some people watched and took pictures and posted them on Weibo.
After the police were identified by the public security department, the bows and arrows used were not under control.
The person in charge said, “This kind of fundraising method is not advocated.”
After being warned by the police at the police station, she had already left the police station.
