There is an appointment in the starry sky 丨 The Gemini meteor shower ushered in a great day on the 14th-Xinhua
Xinhua News Agency, Tianjin, December 12 (Reporter Zhou Runjian) Astronomical science experts introduced that as the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Gemini meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the Northern hemisphere, will usher in a great day on December 14. Friends who like meteor showers can observe it in the second half of the day.
The Gemini meteor shower taken by Beijing astronomy enthusiast Anjiu in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
The parent body of most meteor showers is a periodic comet, but the parent body of the Gemini meteor shower is the 3200-year-old asteroid Faer, which is an Apollo-type asteroid.
The Gemini meteor shower is also the second known meteor shower that is not “conceived” by a comet.
Xiu Lipeng, director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an expert in astronomical science, said that just like New Year blockbusters, the Gemini meteor shower generally appears at the end of the year, and the “release schedule” can last from December 4th to 17th.
The meteor shower is known for its large flow and stability. Together with the Quadrant meteor shower and the Perseus meteor Shower, it is called the three major meteor showers in the Northern Hemisphere.
A distinctive feature of the Gemini meteor shower is that the meteoroids are slow, rich in colors, and there are many fire meteors. It is suitable for both visual and astrophotography beginners to shoot.
The Gemini meteor shower taken by Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jing in Jizhou, Tianjin on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecasts show that this year's Gemini meteor shower will usher in a great time around 15:00 on December 14th. At the extreme time, ZHR (under ideal observation conditions, when the radiation point is directly above the head of the sky, the number of meteors that can be seen per hour) is 150.
Gemini Meteor shower recommended index chart.
“Last year, the Gemini meteor shower of "Falling in the Sky" left a deep impression on people, but this year's Gemini meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the excitement will be discounted a little.
The 14th is the 11th of November of the lunar calendar, and the moon phase is the full moon. The bright moonlight will interfere with the observation. Fortunately, the moon will fall in the second half of the night, and the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower will also rise relatively high.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe them in the hours after midnight, but pay attention to keeping warm from the cold.  ”
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
“It is not recommended to observe in the city. You can choose a place with a high altitude, low light pollution, and a wide field of view facing the northeast in the suburbs or countryside, and then wait patiently until the moon sets. Visual observation can be done.
It should be noted that the Gemini meteor shower has a large flow in all directions, so you don't need to keep staring at the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower when observing.
If friends who like photography want to shoot gorgeous ‘meteor shower blockbusters’, it is best to choose a wide-angle, large-aperture lens, and use a high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
Based on stability and continuity considerations, tripods, spare batteries, and shutter cables are also essential.  ”
Xiu Lipeng reminded.
